{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Luciano Mammino \"Loige\" - Web developer, entrepreneur, fighter, butterfly maker!","author":"Luciano Mammino","siteUrl":"https://loige.co/","twitterProfile":"loige","disqusShortName":"loige"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a8173434-baf4-5b98-9c9d-716949fab516","excerpt":"In the last month I had the pleasure to seeing published two interviews regarding my life as developer with  Node.js  and  JavaScript  and…","timeToRead":1,"headings":[],"html":"<p>In the last month I had the pleasure to seeing published two interviews regarding my life as developer with <a href=\"/tag/node-js\">Node.js</a> and <a href=\"/tag/javascript\">JavaScript</a> and about being a book author with <a href=\"https://www.nodejsdesignpatterns.com\">Node.Js design patterns second edition</a>.</p>\n<p>The first interview was made with the <strong>Packt Publishing team</strong> and it was published in their own website:</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.packtpub.com/books/content/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done\">With Node.js, it’s easy to get things done</a></strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.packtpub.com/books/content/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-815ba.webp 256w,\n/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-85397.webp 512w,\n/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-21246.webp 700w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-d3396.png 256w,\n/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-a37e5.png 512w,\n/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-a3ccc.png 700w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-a3ccc.png\"\n          alt=\"With Node.js, it’s easy to get things done interview image\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/nodejs-its-easy-get-things-done-packt-interview-luciano-mammino-84517584107aa76a0b92b8123011d31f-a3ccc.png\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>The second interview was made by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tompeham\">Thomas Peham</a>, marketing manager at <a href=\"http://usersnap.com/blog/\">UserSnap</a>:</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://usersnap.com/blog/developer-community-luciano-mammino/\">Meet the community: Luciano Mammino, software developer from Sicily</a></strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://usersnap.com/blog/developer-community-luciano-mammino/\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-815ba.webp 256w,\n/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-85397.webp 512w,\n/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-21246.webp 700w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-d3396.png 256w,\n/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-a37e5.png 512w,\n/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-a3ccc.png 700w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-a3ccc.png\"\n          alt=\"Meet the community: Luciano Mammino, software developer from Sicily interview image\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/developer-community-luciano-mammino-usersnap-interview-f99e3090fa2ff0f08f8abacdb61121b6-a3ccc.png\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>I think both interviews turned out to be pretty cool, especially because I had a chance to express my vision about the future of JavaScript and Node.js, technologies on which I am investing most of my time.</p>\n<p>Feel more than welcome to let me know if you share my vision or not here in the comments.</p>\n<p>Until next time!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Two Interviews about Node.js, JavaScript and being a book author","meta_description":null,"slug":"two-interviews-about-node-js-javascript-and-being-a-book-author","author":"Luciano Mammino","tags":["collaboration","node-js","javascript"],"date":"September 25, 2016","dateISO":"2016-09-25T13:24:08.000Z","header_img":{"publicURL":"/static/two-interviews-about-node-js-javascript-and-being-a-book-author-6c78bae0ee94b997d9fa49aa200ffe92.jpg"},"fb_img":{"publicURL":"/static/two-interviews-about-node-js-javascript-and-being-a-book-author-fb-6a6df7fe532b5b24b6003c1b1b48bc02.png"},"tw_img":{"publicURL":"/static/two-interviews-about-node-js-javascript-and-being-a-book-author-tw-b6b39ac01370031a2829203b37deba20.png"}}}},"pageContext":{"tags":["collaboration","node-js","javascript"],"slug":"two-interviews-about-node-js-javascript-and-being-a-book-author","previous":{"timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"I recently wrote a new article in collaboration with one of my favourite web development websites: the amazing  Scotch.io . The article talk about using  React  both on client and on the server (with  Node.js ) in an attempt to build a simple “Universal JavaScript” (a.k.a “Isomorphic”) application. The application is called “Judo Heroes” ( did you even noticed recently that I’m kind of fond of Judo? ) and it showcases some of the best Judo athletes for their number of medals won during the Olympic Games and…","fields":{"slug":"react-on-the-server-for-beginners-build-a-universal-react-and-node-app"},"frontmatter":{"date":"29 August, 2016","title":"React on the Server for Beginners: Build a Universal React and Node App","tags":["node-js","react","collaboration"],"header_img":{"publicURL":"/static/ryoko-tani-universal-javascript-nodejs-react-luciano-mammino-cover-800b14fb31bd9abfa9102aa9a341562d.jpg"}}},"next":{"timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"In the last 2 weeks I add the pleasure to release an article (in two parts) in col